.TH BUNPY-PM 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-pm \- package manager plumbing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy pm
.I verb
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B pm
tree groups the low-level package-manager verbs. Porcelain
commands (
.BR add ", " install ", " remove ", " update ", " outdated ", " why
) call into the same machinery and live at the top level of the
CLI.
.PP
v0.1.2 wires
.BR "pm config" ,
.BR "pm info" ,
and
.BR "pm install-wheel" .
The resolver and the porcelain
.B add
verb land in v0.1.3 and v0.1.5.
.SH VERBS
.TP
.B config
Print the parsed
.I pyproject.toml
as JSON. See
.BR bunpy-pm-config (1).
.TP
.B info
Fetch a PEP 691 project page and print the parsed metadata
as JSON. See
.BR bunpy-pm-info (1).
.TP
.B install-wheel
Install one wheel into site-packages. See
.BR bunpy-pm-install-wheel (1).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy (1),
.BR bunpy-pm-config (1),
.BR bunpy-pm-info (1),
.BR bunpy-pm-install-wheel (1).
